JOHANNESBURG - The anguish and discomfort of hunger is something many South Africans experience daily. It's detrimental to children, many of whom had to become breadwinners at a young age. eNCA's Mawande Kheswa tells the life story of Zandile Mnyandu (31), who became the head of a household as a teen after losing her parents and grandparents. Watch the video above for more on this story.